\fBManaged File Systems\fR

.in 4
Cynosure 2's managed file system driver provides a shallow layer of abstraction over OpenComputers' filesystem component.  This layer provides support for file permissions and modes.

.in 4
These file attributes are stored as the file name, prefixed with a \fB.\fR and postfixed with a \fB.attr\fR - such that the attributes for the following file:

.in 8
\fB\my/bin/ls\m[default]\fR

.in 4
are stored at:

.in 8
\fB\my/bin/.ls.attr\m[default]\fR

.in 4
and the attributes for the following file:

.in 8
\fB\my/root/.shrc\m[default]\fR

.in 4
are stored at:

.in 8
\fB\my/root/..shrc.attr\m[default]\fR


.in 4
The filesystem driver disallows direct modification of these files.  They may only be changed with the \fB\mbsetattr\m[default]\fR, \fB\mbchmod\m[default]\fR, and \fB\mbchown\m[default]\fR system calls.  They may only be accessed with the \fB\mbstat\m[default]\fR system call.
